post_text:
Dear SCPS Families,

We have created a COVID-19 Data Dashboard that will help inform parents, students, staff, and the community about positive cases throughout the school district.

The dashboard is live starting today and can be found by visiting:
https://www.scps.k12.fl.us/covid19/dashboard.stml

Schools impacted by COVID-19 positive cases will be listed along with the total number of employees and students throughout the district for each campus.

The COVID-19 Data Dashboard will be updated as we receive the latest information on confirmed positive cases from the Florida Department of Health in Seminole County.

***Please Note: This info. won't always be a real-time total as there will be partial delays in information reporting as current cases are confirmed and being worked on. Schools and individuals may be made aware of a positive case on their campus prior to it being reflected in this dashboard.

Thank you!

Dear SCPS Families,

We understand many of you have a lot on your minds before making the very best decision for you and your family regarding selection of an educational option for the 2020-2021 school year. In addition, we also understand and empathize that you're having to make these tough decisions in a relatively short timeframe. To help answer many of your questions, staff have created the below FAQ to assist you in your decision-making process: https://www.scps.k12.fl.us/core/fileparse.php/1824/urlt/reopening-options-faq.pdf

post_text: Yesterday, U.S. Congresswoman Stephanie Murphy of Winter Park, Fla., announced Sanford resident and Seminole High School Sanford student Danielle Shenkman as the winner of her 2020 Congressional Art Competition. Murphy recently hosted her third annual art competition for high school students in Florida‚Äôs Seventh Congressional District. A panel of local art teachers reviewed dozens of student submissions and ultimately selected Shenkman‚Äôs piece, Ode to Quarantine, as the winning artwork. Pending federal, Florida and Washington D.C. COVID-19 restrictions, the Congressional Institute‚Äîwhich sponsors the yearly competition‚Äîwill fly Shenkman to Washington, D.C. for a special ceremony alongside the winners of other participating congressional districts across America. Her artwork will be displayed in the U.S. Capitol for an entire year and featured on the official Congressional Art Competition Website: https://www.house.gov/educators-and-students/congressional-art-competition

***SCPS Summer Hours***

SCPS will begin "Summer Hours" starting June 1- July 17. During this time period, SCPS staff will be working on a 10-hour, 4-day work-week, Monday-Thursday and OFF each Friday. Normal SCPS Hours will resume on July 20.

In addition, during this timeframe, SCPS Buildings will only be OPEN on Tuesdays & Thursdays from 10 a.m. - 2 p.m.

Please remember to call ahead and make an appointment. SCPS staff will still be available and working remotely during non-Building OPEN times to assist you Monday-Thursday.

post_text:
Seminole County Virtual School is hosting their 3rd online "Open House" Meeting for families TOMORROW, May 18th @ 7 p.m.

The online "Open House" will give parents an opportunity to learn about the amazing virtual options we offer our SCPS Students, provide you with a a live Q&A session with our SCVS Administrators and Teachers, and provide you additional information about flexible learning opportunities and how to register.

If unable to attend, this evening's meeting, the next sessions are planned for:

Info. Session #4, Tuesday, May 26th @ 1:00 p.m.

If interested in attending tomorrow's info. session, please visit: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfbBem7oB1RT5vxWUlFjPh1fulMmG7DI9u8aG9cK9dTMcHeqw/viewform

Once your email is received, you will be sent a return email with the WebEx Meeting Login Information to attend.

We look forward to seeing you there! (virtually, of course!)

To learn more about SCVS visit: www.SCVS.us

Dear SCPS Families & Staff,

Beginning on Tuesday, March 31st, visitors to our SCPS Educational Support Center (400 E. Lake Mary Blvd., Sanford, FL 32773) must make an appointment at least 24-hours in advance. No walk-in traffic will be allowed until further notice. Appointment Hour times will be from 9 a.m. ‚Äì 3 p.m. Monday thru Friday.

If you do not already know the phone number for the Department or staff you wish to make an advance appointment with, you may contact 407.320.0000 for assistance.

Thank you!

Dear SCPS Families & Staff,

Beginning on Tuesday, March 31st, visitors to our SCPS Educational Support Center (400 E. Lake Mary Blvd., Sanford, FL 32773) must make an appointment at least 24-hours in advance. No walk-in traffic will be allowed until further notice. Appointment Hour times will be from 9 a.m. ‚Äì 3 p.m. Monday thru Friday.

If you do not already know the phone number for the Department or staff you wish to make an advance appointment with, you may contact 407.320.0000 for assistance.

Thank you!
